description:
Aspose.BarCode for .NET is a robust and reliable barcode generation and recognition component, written in managed C#, it allows developers to quickly and easily add barcode generation and recognition functionality to their Microsoft .NET applications (WinForms, ASP.NET and .NET Compact Framework). 

Aspose.BarCode for .NET supports most established barcode standards and barcode specifications. It has the ability to export to multiple image formats including: BMP, EMF, GIF, JPEG, PNG, TIFF and WMF.
releaseNotes:
The following is a list of improvements and improvements and changes in this release of Aspose.BarCode.

Major features

Add support for PatchCode symbology generation (BARCODENET-34008).

Other Improvements and Changes

New Features:
BARCODENET-33849 - Aspose.BarCode API support for Windows Embedded Compact 7
BARCODENET-34062 - Add ability to check license status

Enhancements:
BARCODENET-33136 - code39 barcode not found from scanned tif image
BARCODENET-33406 - Unable to recognize second EAN13 barcode from jpg image
BARCODENET-33817 - Can't generate a Databar Expanded code with a specified string
BARCODENET-33967 - Can't recognize Code39 codes from the JPG file
BARCODENET-34001 - Incorrect recognition of a linear code from JPG image
BARCODENET-34022 - GS1 encoding and decoding logic for nonstandard variants
BARCODENET-34032 - Performance issue while reading PDF417 and Code128 codes
BARCODENET-34043 - Incorrect recognition of Code128 code from the jpg image
BARCODENET-34044 - Can't recognize QR code form the PDF document
BARCODENET-34046 - Can't read Code39 from the tif file
BARCODENET-34051 - EULA 01 December 2014 Update

Exceptions:
BARCODENET-34047 - InvalidOperationException while recognizing an Interleaved2of5 code
summary: Aspose.BarCode for .NET is a robust and reliable barcode generation and recognition component
title: Aspose.BarCode for .NET
